2. Create Clientset via kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n   3. Get typed client via clientset.AppsV1().Deployments(namespace)\n   4. Create Deployment via deploymentsClient.Create(ctx, deployment, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n   5. Update or Delete using similar typed methods with proper context and options\n   ```\n\n   The example demonstrates proper patterns like using context.TODO() for context management, applying metav1.CreateOptions{} for API options, and using retry mechanisms for handling conflicts during updates.\n\nThis three-layer architecture (API types in k8s.io/api, typed clients in client-go, with practical examples) provides the canonical pattern for deploying and managing Kubernetes services programmatically."
